```json
{
  "application": "Spack",
  "details": {
    "scheduler": "Slurm",
    "spack_version": "0.17.3",
    "spack_instance": "cpu",
    "spack_instance_dir": "/cm/shared/apps/spack/0.17.3/cpu",
    "intel_license_file": "40000@elprado.sdsc.edu:40200@elprado.sdsc.edu",
    "spack_package": "intel@19.1.1.217",
    "spack_compiler": "gcc@11.2.0",
    "spack_variants": "+rpath",
    "spack_dependencies": ""
  }
}
```

This script uses Spack to install the Intel compiler version 19.1.1.217 on a system using Slurm for job scheduling. The script sets up the environment and configuration for Spack, defines the specific package and compiler to install, and uses Slurm resources to efficiently install the package. It also includes checks for successful installation and configures the Lmod environment to manage the installed package.
